    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1350"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1350">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/141.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Willard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs requests me to thank the Department of State for the
                    prompt assistance rendered by our Consul at Chihuahua and Consular agent at
                    Torreon to Cardenas now at El Paso. He earnestly requests that said Consuls be
                    permitted to further assist Cardenas in establishing the fact that the sixty
                    self-supporting Spanish families and the ten families supported by charity, all
                    in El Paso, have taken no part in Mexican affairs, and thereby secure such
                    guarantees from the revolutionist commanders as will justify these families in
                    returning to their home.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
